      • getEntryStartBytes

        public BytesAndCheckSum getEntryStartBytes(boolean incremental,
                                           boolean leadingSoh,
                                           int mdEntryTypeIndex,
                                           boolean deleteAction)
        Description copied from interface: IFixFieldConstants
        Gets bytes and checksum associated with start of a market data entry for an MDEntryType with the given index, in either an incremental refresh or full refresh (snapshot) market data message.

        If leadingSoh is true, the bytes start with a leading soh (thus terminating a previous entry).

        No trailing soh is included.

        For incremental market data messages, this consists of the MDUpdateAction field (set to Constants.MDUPDATEACTION_New or Constants.MDUPDATEACTION_Delete depending on deleteAction) plus the MDEntryType field. In other words... 

           [soh] 279= updateAction soh 269= mdEntryType

        For full refresh market data messages, this just consists of the MDEntryType field. In other words... 

           [soh] 269= mdEntryType
        Specified by:
        getEntryStartBytes in interface IFixFieldConstants
        Parameters:
        incremental - True if we want bytes for an incremental refresh market data message - otherwise full refresh (snapshot).
        leadingSoh - True if we want bytes to include a leading soh byte.
        mdEntryTypeIndex - Index of MDEntryType value.
        deleteAction - True if UpdateAction should be delete - only relevant for incremental updates - ignored otherwise.
        Returns:
        Bytes and checksum of those bytes.

      • getTagBytes

        public BytesAndCheckSum getTagBytes(int fixTag,
                                    boolean leadingSoh)
        Description copied from interface: IFixFieldConstants
        Gets bytes and checksum for the given FIX tag.

        If leadingSoh is true the bytes start with an soh. There is no trailing soh.

        Returns bytes and checksum for: 

           [soh] fixTag=
        Specified by:
        getTagBytes in interface IFixFieldConstants
        Parameters:
        fixTag - Tag number whose bytes are required.
        leadingSoh - True if we want bytes to include a leading soh byte.
        Returns:
        Bytes and checksum of those bytes.
